<section id="anglr-language-syntax">
    <h1>Anglr Syntax Rules for C# Language</h1>
    <hr />
    <h4>Introduction</h4>
    <p>
        This paragraph introduces complete set of Anglr syntax rules for C# 8 programming language. C# parser, which is made using these rules,
        can be used to produce concrete syntax tree for any C# source code file. C# program following these syntax rules,
        should be used to parse single C# source file or the whole directory of C# source code files. The result is a list of concrete
        syntax trees. For every source file parsed without syntax errors there is exactly one syntax tree in the list.
    </p>
